title: Newnan, East Coweta roll in first round
text:
Newnan, East Coweta roll in first round Friday, October 09, 2015 Comments 
Top-seed Newnan and No. 2-seed East Coweta are on a collision course to meet at least once Saturday in the Area 3- tournament. 
Both teams stayed in the winnersâ€™ bracket with easy wins Thursday during the opening day of the tournament at East Coweta High School. 
The Lady Cougars rolled to an easy win over No. 8 seed South Cobb (25-7, 25-11), while East Coweta quickly beat No. 7 Langston Hughes (25-7, 25-6). 
A few things still have to happen before Newnan and East Coweta can meet Satur- day. They include winning respective sec- ond-round matches at 9:30 a.m.. 
Newnan takes on Douglas County, while East Coweta plays Campbell. 
From there, the double-elimination tournament continues throughout the day Saturday with the best of five finals set for 2 p.m. 
Newnan earned the No. 1 seed in the event after knocking off East Coweta and dethroning the Lady Indians at the Coweta County championship for the first time in three years in a match that also counting the Region 3- standings. More
